# ClickNBack – Guided API Tour
# ============================
#
# A nine-step walkthrough of the full cashback lifecycle, designed for
# recruiters, hiring managers, and technical reviewers who want to
# experience the product before reading the code.
#
# Requirements:
#   VS Code with the REST Client extension (humao.rest-client), or
#   IntelliJ IDEA / WebStorm (built-in HTTP client).
#
# Instructions:
#   1. Run the login requests in Steps 1 and 3 first.
#   2. Copy each returned access_token and paste it (prefixed with "Bearer ")
#      into @adminToken or @userToken below.
#   3. Execute the remaining requests in order.
#
# The live API resets nightly at 03:00 UTC — any data you create will not
# persist beyond that. Change external_id in Step 7 on each run to avoid
# a 409 Conflict from a previous session.
#
# Full guided tour with context: https://jerosanchez.com/posts/20260323-before-you-ask/

@baseUrl = https://clicknback.com/api/v1

# Paste fresh tokens here after running the login steps below.
# These are intentionally empty — the steps tell you when to fill them.
@adminToken = Bearer PASTE_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE
@userToken  = Bearer PASTE_USER_TOKEN_HERE

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# STEP 1 — Admin Login
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Carol is the pre-seeded platform admin.
# The JWT payload carries role=admin, which unlocks merchant management and
# platform-wide visibility. Role is verified by a stateless middleware on
# every request — no DB lookup per call.
#
# → Run this request, copy the access_token from the response,
#   paste it as "Bearer <token>" into @adminToken above.

### Login as admin (carol)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "carol@clicknback.com",
  "password": "Str0ng!Pass"
}

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# STEP 2 — Browse Merchants (Admin View)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Admins can see all merchants regardless of activation status.
# Only active merchants are eligible for cashback — inactive merchants are
# excluded from the offers visible to users (see Step 6).
# This endpoint returns 403 Forbidden if called with a user token.

### List all merchants (admin-only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/merchants
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

### Filter to active merchants only
GET {{baseUrl}}/merchants?active=true
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# STEP 3 — User Login
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Alice is a pre-seeded user with existing wallet history:
#   pending_balance=19.05  — cashback from purchases awaiting confirmation
#   available_balance=15.00 — confirmed cashback ready to withdraw
#   paid_balance=50.00      — cashback already paid out
#
# This pre-populated state lets you see the three-bucket model immediately
# without waiting for the background job to run.
#
# → Run this request, copy the access_token from the response,
#   paste it as "Bearer <token>" into @userToken above.

### Login as user (alice, pre-seeded with wallet history)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@clicknback.com",
  "password": "Str0ng!Pass"
}

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# STEP 4 — Self-Register (Optional)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Registration is public — no token required.
# Password policy: 8+ chars, at least one uppercase, lowercase, digit, special.
# The response includes your new user's id — you would need it in Step 7
# to ingest a purchase on your own account instead of alice's.
#
# Note: change the email on each run (emails are unique; re-registration
# returns 409 EMAIL_ALREADY_REGISTERED).

### Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "recruiter@example.com",
  "password": "Str0ng!Pass"
}

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# STEP 5 — Browse All Offers (Admin View)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Admins see all offers — active, inactive, and those with expired date ranges.
# Each offer is linked to a specific merchant and specifies a cashback type
# (percent or fixed), optional monthly cap, and validity window.

### List all offers (admin sees full unfiltered list)
GET {{baseUrl}}/offers
Authorization: {{adminToken}}

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# STEP 6 — Browse Active Offers (User View)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Users only see offers where BOTH the offer AND the parent merchant are active.
# This endpoint enforces the business rule at the query level: an inactive
# merchant removes all its offers from user visibility automatically.
# Response is paginated; offset and limit query params are supported.

### List active offers (user-facing, both merchant and offer must be active)
GET {{baseUrl}}/offers/active
Authorization: {{userToken}}

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# STEP 7 — Ingest a Purchase
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Purchases are ingested immediately (optimistic ingest). On receipt, three
# things happen atomically in a single DB transaction:
#   1. A Purchase row is created with status=pending.
#   2. A CashbackTransaction row is created with status=pending.
#   3. The user's pending_balance in the wallet is incremented.
#
# A background job then simulates bank reconciliation asynchronously.
# When it runs, confirmed purchases move cashback from pending → available;
# rejected ones remove the pending amount.
#
# Idempotency: external_id is a UNIQUE constraint at the DB level.
# Re-submitting the same external_id returns 409 Conflict — no double-crediting.
# Change external_id on each run to avoid this.
#
# user_id must match the authenticated user (alice's id is shown below).
# Shoply (5% cashback) is the active merchant used here; a 75.00 EUR purchase
# will credit 3.75 EUR to alice's pending balance.

### Ingest a purchase (change external_id on each run to avoid 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/purchases
Authorization: {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "external_id": "qs_tour_001",
  "user_id": "b7e2c1a2-4f3a-4e2b-9c1a-8d2e3f4b5c6d",
  "merchant_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-4a7b-8c9d-0e1f2a3b4c5d",
  "amount": 75.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

### Retry with the same external_id — returns 409 Conflict (idempotency in action)
POST {{baseUrl}}/purchases
Authorization: {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "external_id": "qs_tour_001",
  "user_id": "b7e2c1a2-4f3a-4e2b-9c1a-8d2e3f4b5c6d",
  "merchant_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-4a7b-8c9d-0e1f2a3b4c5d",
  "amount": 75.00,
  "currency": "EUR"
}

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# STEP 8 — Check Wallet Balance
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# The wallet tracks three balance buckets:
#   pending   — cashback from purchases awaiting background confirmation
#   available — confirmed cashback ready to withdraw
#   paid      — cashback already paid out via a withdrawal
#
# After Step 7, alice's pending_balance will have increased by 3.75 EUR.
# As the background job runs, confirmed purchases move cashback from
# pending → available. The three buckets stay consistent across concurrent
# wallet operations via SELECT FOR UPDATE row-level locking.

### Get wallet summary (the three balance buckets)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/wallet
Authorization: {{userToken}}

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# STEP 9 — View Purchase History
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Shows alice's full purchase history enriched with merchant names, amounts,
# cashback amounts, and per-transaction cashback status.
# As the background job confirms purchases over time, watch status transition
# from pending → confirmed. Filter by status to isolate each state.

### All purchases (default pagination)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/purchases
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### Filter: confirmed purchases only (cashback moved to available)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/purchases?status=confirmed
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### Filter: pending purchases only (awaiting background job)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/purchases?status=pending
Authorization: {{userToken}}

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# BONUS — Wallet Transaction Log
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# A full append-only log of all cashback credits and reversals for the user,
# ordered newest first. Useful for seeing the full history of balance changes
# in both directions (credit on confirmation, reversal on rejection).

### Wallet transaction history (limit/offset pagination)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me/wallet/transactions
Authorization: {{userToken}}
